    "content": "Scott, we're on Step 7 now (Steps 4-6 are complete, including clarify-as-next-action from Step 5). Carson is driving Step 7 (Clarify as Project).\n\nRegarding your domain sketch: the existing `clarify_as_next_action` ended up as a service-layer function rather than a pure domain function. The transformation happens directly in `inbox_service.rs` line 142: `NextAction::new(user_id.clone(), context_id, item.title().clone())`. No separate domain-level `clarify_as_next_action` function was extracted.\n\nFor Step 7, `clarify_as_project` is more complex -- it creates two entities (Project from inbox item title + NextAction linked to that project with a user-provided title and context). The question is: should Carson extract a pure domain function for this, or follow the established pattern of handling the transformation in the service layer?\n\nMy recommendation: follow the existing pattern (service layer) for consistency. The transaction envelope (find inbox item, insert project, insert next action, delete inbox item) is inherently a service concern, and the domain types (`Project::new()` and `NextAction::new_for_project()`) already exist and are well-tested. Adding a pure domain function that just calls these constructors would add indirection without much value.\n\nWhat's your view? Carson will need this guidance before he starts coding."
